title.narrative: Productive Safety Net Program/ Development Food Assistance Program - FHI

description.narrative: (Ethiopia): DFAP-FH is an implementing mechanism designed to support the Productive Safety Net Program (PSNP) in nine districts of Amhara Region to improve the food security status of food insecure household through Food-For-Work programs.With FY 2015 funds, DFAP-FH will benefit nearly 100,000 people by distributing 15,648 metric tons of food to improve community resiliency to shocks. DFAP-FH will improve sanitation facilities for 6,716 beneficiaries, improve drinking water supply for 9,469 households, rehabilitate 10,814 hectares of land and construct 275 km of roads to improve access to social services. The activity will train 1,000 people on Disaster Risk Management and develop early warning systems in 206 communities. In order to increase access to nutritious foods for families, DFAP-FH will target 1,454 women with agriculture trainings, provide 4,500 women with seedlings and 7,200 women will use new technologies or practices to increase their access to nutritious foods.Natural resource management activities will include watershed rehabilitation, reforestation, area closures, groundwater recharge, and soil fertility improvement; protection against erosion, flooding and landslides; and increases to vegetation cover. Smallholder production activities will focus on small-scale irrigation for high value crops, such as fruits and vegetables. CRS will continue to promote technologies and management practices which increase efficient use of water resources. These activities will promote sustainable economic opportunities that are suited to the physical environment while addressing the impact of climate change and increase beneficiaries' resilience to shocks.
